  <h3 id="checkout-page">Create a discount code</h3>
  <p>After you've created a product, you can create discount codes to offer a discount to your customers.</p>
  <p>Creating discount codes is easy—just go to the <a href="https://gumroad.com/checkout/discounts">Discounts tab on the Checkout page</a>. </p>
  <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/657b13f8a55b5524fb50d6a4/file-EentR7IlvA.png" %></figure>
  <p>Click "New discount" to get started. We auto-generate a discount code for you, but you can replace it with your custom code.</p>
  <p><span>Note:</span> The code can contain only numbers and letters.</p>
  <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/65c309278106ae1c4ab6f392/file-GAk6eFEPyf.png" %></figure>
  <p>Choose the product(s) you want this discount code to apply to, or check “All products” if you want it to apply to all your products.</p>
  <p>Enter the discount code and the amount or percentage off of your full price.</p>
  <h3 id="Allow-customers-to-enter-discount-codes-IN4wU">Allow customers to enter discount codes</h3>
  <p>To show the discount code input box on the checkout page, toggle  "Only if a discount is available" in the <a href="https://gumroad.com/checkout/form">Checkout form</a> tab, otherwise, it will only be possible to apply a discount code by using a <a href="270-url-parameters">URL parameter</a>.</p>
  <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/657b142ea55b5524fb50d6a5/file-RPDfnvrDVr.png" %></figure>
  <h3 id="Discounts-for-memberships-_Pxb_">Discounts for memberships</h3>
  <p>When a discount code applies to a membership, choose how long it lasts under <b>Discount duration for memberships</b>:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Forever</b> — applies to the first charge and every renewal.</li>
    <li><b>Once (first billing period only)</b> — applies only to the first charge. Renewals charge full price.</li>
  </ul>
  <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/64a11a8674f970393a8b0b36/file-GRMdcSBATo.png" %></figure>
  <p>Want the opposite — full price up front, discount on renewals? Set that up under <a href="#limit-to-existing-customers">Limit to existing customers</a>.</p>
  <h3 id="Discount-code-customization-nlf76">Discount code customization</h3>
  <p>You can customize a discount code by setting these parameters:</p>
  <br>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p><b>Limit quantity</b></p>
      <p>Limit the total number of times this code can be used by setting a “Limit quantity”. By default, the code can be used an unlimited number of times. This limits the overall uses of the code, not the number of uses by a specific customer.</p>
      <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/65c30a53ffa21909875f09e0/file-4Nb6iBmdkR.png" %></figure>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><b>Limit the validity period</b></p>
      <p>Schedule discount codes in advance by setting a validity period. This allows you to create discount codes ahead of time and also expire them without losing access to revenue or usage stats. This can be useful for time-limited offers or promotions.</p>
      <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/65c309580a12eb325db176e9/file-88EykczAUI.png" %></figure>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><b>Set a minimum qualifying amount</b></p>
      <p>Set a minimum $ amount to allow a discount only when the customer's total spend for the discount’s product(s) exceeds this amount.</p>
      <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/65c30a740a12eb325db176eb/file-Xb8iyKk30M.png" %></figure>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><b>Set a minimum quantity</b></p>
      <p>Incentivize your customers to purchase multiple quantities of a product by setting a minimum quantity. These codes will apply only if the customer is purchasing a quantity greater than or equal to the set minimum. </p>
      <p><b>Please note:</b> The intended product(s) must have the “Allow customers to choose a quantity” setting toggled on for your customers to be able to utilize this code. You can do this from the product’s edit page.</p>
      <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/65c30a93ffa21909875f09e1/file-fedhaSLrxl.png" %></figure>
      <br>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h3 id="limit-to-existing-customers">Limit to existing customers</h3>
  <p>Restrict a discount code to buyers who already own one of your products. Open the discount, scroll to <b>Settings</b>, and turn on <b>Limit to existing customers</b>. Under <b>Must have purchased</b>, pick the product (or products) the buyer must already own for the code to apply.</p>
  <figure><%= image_tag "help_center/discount-existing-customers.png", alt: "Limit to existing customers toggle with the Must have purchased product picker" %></figure>
  <p>A few common setups:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Discount renewals, not the first charge.</b> On a membership, pick the same membership product under <b>Must have purchased</b>. The first charge isn't discounted — the buyer doesn't own the product yet — but every renewal is. This is the simplest way to give subscribers introductory pricing.</li>
    <li><b>Reward repeat buyers.</b> Pick Product A under <b>Must have purchased</b>, then set the discount to apply to Product B. Buyers who already own A get the discount on B.</li>
    <li><b>Scale the discount with tenure.</b> See <b>Tiered discounts by ownership duration</b> below.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 id="tiered-discounts-by-ownership-duration">Tiered discounts by ownership duration</h4>
  <p>Check <b>Tiered discounts by ownership duration</b> to vary the percentage by how long the buyer has owned the product. Each tier covers a range of months, and the percentage kicks in once the buyer crosses into that range.</p>
  <figure><%= image_tag "help_center/discount-tiered-ownership.png", alt: "Two-tier discount: 0 to 12 months at 0%, 12+ months at 50%" %></figure>
  <p>Example — introductory pricing on a $50/year membership:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><b>0–12 months</b>, 0% discount → the buyer pays $50 in year 1, before any renewal.</li>
    <li><b>12+ months</b>, 50% discount → the buyer pays $25 on every renewal from year 2 onward.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Click <b>Add tier</b> to add another range. Tiers sort by starting month automatically.</p>
  <p>A few things to know:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The first tier must start at 0 months.</li>
    <li>Tiered discounts require the <b>Percentage</b> discount type — fixed amounts aren't supported.</li>
    <li>You can't combine tiers with <b>Discount duration for memberships</b>. When tiers are on, that option is hidden — the tiers control the schedule.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 id="edit-discount-codes">Edit discount codes</h3>
  <p>Click any discount you want to edit, and a side panel will open. </p>
  <p>Under "Products", click the share button to copy a product-specific link. This copies the URL to your <a href="136-find-your-products-url">Gumroad product</a> with "/{yourdiscountcode}" attached.</p>
  <figure><%= image_tag "https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/docs/assets/5c4657ad2c7d3a66e32d763f/images/657b140e4773693a6d83e080/file-JRg3rVoT9r.png" %></figure>
  <p>Once you click on the discounted link, you will see that the original price is crossed out, and the discounted price is displayed next to it. This only displays if a discount code is applied from the product-specific link. Currently, this is the only way to show slashed prices.</p>
  <figure><%= image_tag "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/6uHGn-GggrtKugV2fc3VLzfq6gRBxad8U1E5Q2SMs04eRvUAfktDmKg7qCECcX-vcukIPXtsG_ZcNbmn-UtoLlCgT_MF6DYNqrCjNolpv-AzRnwzXRMAHOibKoAFY4ysHRQy000KN8-dp5ybEhU4Gyo" %></figure>
  <h3 id="FAQs-pJIfb">FAQs</h3>
  <p><strong>Q: How do I embed a discount code in my product's URL? </strong></p>
  <p>Attach it to the end of the URL! For example: <a href="https://username.gumroad.com/%7BYourProductID%7D">https://username.gumroad.com/{YourProductID}</a> becomes <a href="https://username.gumroad.com/%7BYourProductID%7D/%7BYourOfferCode%7D">https://username.gumroad.com/{YourProductID}/{YourDiscountCode}</a></p>
  <p><strong>Q: Can I embed a discount code in my custom domain?</strong></p>
  <p>Yes! Similar to how it's done on the Gumroad domain, you'll have to add the coupon code at the end of the custom URL: <a href="128-discount-codes">https://</a> {YourCustomDomain}/{YourProductID}/{YourDiscountCode}</p>
  <p><strong>Q: Can discount codes be used on top of one another? </strong></p>
  <p>Only one code can be used per product.</p>
  <p><span>Q: Can my customer use Purchasing Power Parity in combination with a discount code?</span></p>
  <p>Gumroad's system is designed to give the customer the best possible discount, so if the PPP discount is greater, it will be applied instead of the discount code.</p>
  <p>If the customer still wishes to use the discount code instead of the PPP discount, you would need to disable PPP in your settings. However, this would affect all customers, not just the ones trying to use the offer code.</p>
  <p><b>Q: Can a discount code be added to an affiliate link?</b></p>
  <p>You can combine an affiliate link with a discount code:</p>
  <p>https://{Your_Username}.<a href="http://gumroad.com/l/%7BYourProductID%7D/%7BYourDiscountCode%7D?affiliate_id=%7BAffiliate_ID%7D">gumroad.com/l/{YourProductID}/{YourDiscountCode}?affiliate_id={Affiliate_ID}</a></p>
  <p>The affiliate ID can be found in the affiliate link the number after the /a/.</p>
